The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 World Briefs

 Afghan violence 

 Kandahar, April 15 (Reuters): Afghan forces and coalition helicopter gunships attacked a suspected Taliban hideout in Afghanistan, triggering a fierce battle that killed 41 militants. 

 Six Afghan policemen were also killed. 

 Khodorkovsky 

 Moscow (Reuters): Mikhail Khodorkovsky, the founder of Russias Yukos oil company, was slashed with a knife in the Siberian prison where he is serving an eight-year sentence, a statement on his website said on Saturday. 

 Gaza salaries 

 Gaza (Reuters): Dozens of Palestinian security men stormed a government building in the Gaza Strip on Saturday demanding the Hamas-led administration pay salaries. 




